Page title
- Grade

Table
- Column headers: When measuring | Use | Which is defined as | Illus.

Row 1
- When measuring: The height of a structure on land with natural slope ≤ 10%
- Use: Existing Grade
- Which is defined as: for each building or structure, the lowest point of adjacent ground elevation prior to grading or fill
- Illus.: Fig 44 on this page

Row 2
- When measuring: The height of a structure on land with natural slope > 10%
- Use: Grade
- Which is defined as: adjacent ground elevation of the finished or existing grade, whichever is lower—at any point of the structure
- Illus.: Fig 45 on this page

Row 3
- When measuring: A daylight plane
- Use: Average grade
- Which is defined as: average of the grade at the midpoint of the building and the grade at the closest point on the abutting site
- Illus.: Figs 20–21 pp. 26–27
